 :BLOB: 1. n. [acronym: Binary Large OBject] Used by database people to refer
to any random large block of bits that needs to be stored in a database, such
as a picture or sound file. The essential point about a BLOB is that it's an
object that cannot be interpreted within the database itself. 2. v. To
{mailbomb} someone by sending a BLOB him/her; esp. used as a mild threat. "If
that program crashes again, I'm going to BLOB the core dump to you."